<subSubSection id="C32DF8BD965BFFF2FF2710BB3834FCAE" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B88AB36965BFFF2FF2710BB3B45FD64" blockId="2.[178,1086,219,651]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">
Description: Length: 
<quantity id="4CCF06D3965BFFF2FE6A10BB3B56FF1F" box="[511,601,219,241]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
; length of fore-body: 
<quantity id="4CCF06D3965BFFF2FCCB10BB3AB6FF1F" box="[862,953,219,240]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787" unit="mm" value="4.3">4.3 mm</quantity>
. Head, and pronotum black, elytra reddish brown, abdomen dark brown (in 
<specimenCount id="9D3160BF965BFFF2FCD610983ABCFEE1" box="[835,947,248,270]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
the abdomen is black and the elytra somewhat infuscate posteriorly); mouthparts, antennae and legs brown. Fore-body: 
<figureCitation id="130CB7B3965BFFF2FE15115338CFFEA6" box="[384,448,307,329]" captionStart="Figs 3-4" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1497,1519]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,238,1434]" captionTargetId="figure-80@11.[178,1085,212,1463]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 3-4: Fore-body (fb), head (h), aedoeagus in lateral view (al), aedoeagus in ventral view (av), male sternite VII (s7), male sternite VIII of: 3: P. cuccodoroi; 4: P. duplopunctata Fig. 3: P. cuccodoroi 3fb 3al 3av Fig. 4: P. duplopunctata 4fb 4h 4al 4av" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5873562" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5873562/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
fb. Head transverse (1 x 
<quantity id="4CCF06D3965BFFF2FD4711523A3BFEA7" box="[722,820,306,328]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787" unit="mm" value="1.35">1.35 mm</quantity>
), the eyes larger than in preceding two species, much longer than temples; anterior margin with a pair of foveate punctures, 2 punctures on inner margins of eyes set closer together than in preceding species, 3-4 punctures near postero-lateral angles, the disc with a pair of large punctures some distance from inner margins of eyes (in the 
<typeStatus id="548C1594965BFFF2FD6D11C83A5EFE51" box="[760,849,424,446]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">holotype</typeStatus>
the are two foveate depressions between these punctures, in all forming an arcuate transverse row of four). Pronotum slightly transverse (1.3 x 
<quantity id="4CCF06D3965BFFF2FDBF11823B72FE17" box="[554,637,482,504]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.4 mm</quantity>
), the sides a little retracted posteriorly, the postero-lateral angles more broadly rounded than in the preceding two species; discal series of 5 small punctures, lateral series of 2-4 punctures. Elytra slightly elongate (1.5 x 
<quantity id="4CCF06D3965BFFF2FF27125A3808FDBF" box="[178,263,570,592]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.4 mm</quantity>
), with only 2 discal series of 4-5 punctures, the interstriae with more or less serially aligned micro-punctures. Abdomen with sparse, fine, slightly asperate punctures, the interstices devoid of microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B88AB36965BFFF2FF2712FA3834FCAE" blockId="2.[178,1086,666,834]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">
Male: posterior margin of sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="130CB7B3965BFFF2FDF512FA3BA4FD5F" box="[608,683,666,688]" captionStart="Figs 3-4" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1497,1519]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,238,1434]" captionTargetId="figure-80@11.[178,1085,212,1463]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 3-4: Fore-body (fb), head (h), aedoeagus in lateral view (al), aedoeagus in ventral view (av), male sternite VII (s7), male sternite VIII of: 3: P. cuccodoroi; 4: P. duplopunctata Fig. 3: P. cuccodoroi 3fb 3al 3av Fig. 4: P. duplopunctata 4fb 4h 4al 4av" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5873562" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5873562/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">Fig. 3s</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="130CB7B3965BFFF2FD3E12FA3BB6FD5F" box="[683,697,666,688]" captionStart="Figs 7-8" captionStartId="13.[178,218,1516,1538]" captionTargetBox="[193,1076,226,1464]" captionTargetId="figure-84@13.[178,1085,212,1481]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 7-8: Fore-body (fb), aedoeagus in lateral view (al), aedoeagus in ventral view (av), male sternite VII (s7), male sternite VIII (s8) of: 7: P. ivani; 8: P. longicollis Fig. 7: P. ivani 7fb 7al 7av 7s7 Fig. 8: P. longicollis 8fb 8al 8av 8s8" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5873570" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5873570/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">7</figureCitation>
) with a very small shallow median emargination, the surface of sternite longitudinally impressed in front of emargination, the sides with a fringe of black bristles forming a comb of short teeth near emargination, the bristles becoming progressively longer and sparser laterally; finely bordered emargination of sternite VIII extending to about 6 /16 
<superScript id="7C42067E965BFFF2FD4313683BE6FCF9" attach="left" box="[726,745,776,790]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">ths</superScript>
the length of sternite; aedoeagus: 
<figureCitation id="130CB7B3965BFFF2FF27134C39FFFCAD" box="[178,240,812,834]" captionStart="Figs 3-4" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1497,1519]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,238,1434]" captionTargetId="figure-80@11.[178,1085,212,1463]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 3-4: Fore-body (fb), head (h), aedoeagus in lateral view (al), aedoeagus in ventral view (av), male sternite VII (s7), male sternite VIII of: 3: P. cuccodoroi; 4: P. duplopunctata Fig. 3: P. cuccodoroi 3fb 3al 3av Fig. 4: P. duplopunctata 4fb 4h 4al 4av" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5873562" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5873562/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">Figs 3</figureCitation>
al, 3av.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32DF8BD965BFFF2FF2713323A77FC4D" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B88AB36965BFFF2FF2713323A77FC4D" blockId="2.[178,1085,850,930]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">
This new member of the Nigerrima group differs from all other species known from New 
<collectingCountry id="F320EBA6965BFFF2FF27130F39F4FC6A" box="[178,251,879,901]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="2" pageNumber="1787">Guinea</collectingCountry>
